[[File:Ysalamiri_cage.jpg|thumb|right|250px|A ysalamiri cage mounted on a Mobile Defense Unit.]]
The '''ysalamiri cage''' was found on [[Zann Consortium/Legends|Zann Consortium]] [[Mobile Defense Unit]]s. The Consortium used these cages, each of which contained a single [[Ysalamiri/Legends|ysalamir]] from [[Myrkr/Legends|Myrkr]] to make bubbles within [[The Force/Legends|the Force]], making the areas they contained impossible for [[Force-sensitive/Legends|users]] of the Force to access their power. This gave Consortium forces an advantage when encountering [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] beings.

{{Tech-stub}}

==Notable uses==
The only true canonical use of this was during the [[Raid on the Imperial Archive|Theft on Coruscant]]. During gameplay, ysalamiri cages are only buildable when Myrkr is under Zann Consortium control.

